.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-PLAN 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.12.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-plan \- Build a review\-first dashboard reconcile plan from a local dashboard export tree against live Grafana.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard plan [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Build a review\-first dashboard reconcile plan from a local dashboard export tree against live Grafana.
.PP
Use this when you want to understand what a dashboard export would mean against a target Grafana before deciding whether to import, re\-export, prune remote\-only dashboards, or inspect dependency warnings.
.SH BEFORE / AFTER
.IP \(bu 2
Before: dashboard import and diff flows could show pieces of local\-vs\-live state, but there was no one dashboard\-specific reconcile review document.
.IP \(bu 2
After: dashboard plan shows create, update, remote\-only, delete\-candidate, blocked, and warning rows in one review model.
.IP \(bu 2
JSON output is structured for CI and future TUI review. Rows include stable actionId, status, changed fields, target evidence, dependency hints, and review hints. Folder permission rows also include subject, permission, and inherited markers.
.IP \(bu 2
Multi\-org export roots are resolved from exported org IDs, not from file\-system folder names alone.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-input\-dir
local dashboard export root or dashboard variant directory.
.TP
.B \-\-input\-type
choose raw or source. Use source for prompt\-lane exports.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id
plan against one explicit Grafana org.
.TP
.B \-\-use\-export\-org
route a combined multi\-org export root by exported org IDs instead of a single explicit target org.
.TP
.B \-\-only\-org\-id
limit the plan to one or more exported source org IDs.
.TP
.B \-\-create\-missing\-orgs
keep missing destination orgs as review\-only would\-create entries in the plan.
.TP
.B \-\-prune
show remote\-only dashboards as would\-delete candidates. Without this flag they remain extra\-remote.
.TP
.B \-\-include\-folder\-permissions
include folder permission drift review from raw/permissions.json.
.TP
.B \-\-folder\-permission\-match
choose uid or uid\-then\-path. The default is uid; uid\-then\-path falls back to folder path only when the exported UID is not found.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
choose text, table, or json.
.TP
.B \-\-show\-same
include unchanged rows in text and table output.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-columns, \-\-list\-columns, \-\-no\-header
tune table output.
.SH SUCCESS CRITERIA
.IP \(bu 2
create and update candidates are visible before import
.IP \(bu 2
remote\-only dashboards are called out without deleting anything by default
.IP \(bu 2
provisioned or managed targets are blocked before an operator treats the plan as ready
.IP \(bu 2
Git Sync\-managed targets are visible as source\-owned targets, so the next step is repository review rather than API replay
.IP \(bu 2
unresolved datasource references and folder issues are surfaced as review hints
.IP \(bu 2
exported folder permission differences are visible before any import or restore workflow
.IP \(bu 2
missing destination orgs can stay as review\-only would\-create entries when \-\-create\-missing\-orgs is set
.SH FAILURE CHECKS
.IP \(bu 2
if the plan points at the wrong org, confirm \-\-org\-id or the selected profile
.IP \(bu 2
if \-\-use\-export\-org is needed, make sure the export root is a combined multi\-org export and that Basic auth is configured
.IP \(bu 2
if \-\-only\-org\-id is set, confirm the exported source org IDs are present in the export metadata
.IP \(bu 2
if delete candidates appear unexpectedly, rerun without \-\-prune and inspect extra\-remote rows first
.IP \(bu 2
if dependency hints appear, confirm the target Grafana has the expected datasource inventory and folder structure
.IP \(bu 2
if folder permission rows are blocked, confirm the exported folder UID exists on the target or rerun with \-\-folder\-permission\-match uid\-then\-path
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Build a review\-first dashboard reconcile plan from a local dashboard export tree against live Grafana.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard plan --profile prod --input-dir ./dashboards/raw
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1)
